      "span_text": "Most patients with ADHD-like symptoms were assessed before and after treatment using the ADHD Rating Scale (ARS) to evaluate the severity of their symptoms.  Severity of and improvement in symptoms were evaluated prior to administration of atypical antipsychotics and at every visit using the Clinical Global ImpressionSeverity (CGI-S: 1=not ill, 7=extremely ill) and the CGIImprovement (CGI-I: 1=very much improved, 7=very much worse) scales."
